name: InDev Version
desc:
Use this simple Kanban template to keep the engineering team on the same page and moving through work fluidly. 

1. Break down the roadmap by adding tasks as cards to the **Backlog** list. 

2. Move the cards one-by-one through **Design** as they becomes more fleshed out. *Pro tip:* You can enable Power-ups for your favorite design tools like [Figma](https://trello.com/power-ups/59b2e7611e6ece0b35eac16a/figma) or [Invision](https://trello.com/power-ups/596f2cb2d279152540b2bb31), in order to easily link and view designs without switching context.

3. When a card is fully specced out and designs are attached, move it to **To Do** for engineers to pick up. 

4. Engineers move cards to **Doing** and assign themselves to the cards, so the whole team stays informed of who is working on what.

5. Cards then move through **Code Review** when they're ready for a second set of eyes. The team can set a **List Limit** (with the List Limit Power-up) on the number of cards in Code Review, as a visual indicator for when the team needs to prioritize reviews rather than picking up new work. 

6. Once cards move through **Testing** and eventually ship to production, move them to **Done** and celebrate!

listing.name: Export & Sync (Trello to Google Sheets)
listing.description:
###🚀 Quickly export cards from your entire Trello board directly to Google Sheets with support for all custom fields. 

###🔁 Your spreadsheet will update in real-time whenever cards are added or changed.

###📊 Share up-to-date reports for stakeholders without copy-paste or CSVs.

Powered by Unito, the team behind Mirror (50k+ installs) and Board Sync (50k+ installs).


![Export & Sync Animation](https://unito.io/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/ExportandSync-MAY23.gif)

---

## How it works
Combine the reporting power of Google Sheets with the smooth project management of a Trello board in just a few clicks.

Export & Sync gets Trello data from your boards into Google Sheets and keeps your cards in sync with spreadsheet rows, including all custom fields. 

If a label or due date changes after your initial export, that gets automatically synced back to Google Sheets so your report is always accurate.

No more stakeholders chasing you down for the latest details.


## Watch a demo

[![Image name](https://unito.io/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Trello-Connect-Your-Tools.png)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6ZlcT9CkpuU&ab_channel=Unito)

## Features and benefits
### Eliminate manual data entry
Just connect your Trello board and Google account to Unito, then in a few clicks you’ll have your export ready. 

### Up-to-date spreadsheet reports in one place
No need to chase down multiple spreadsheets or triple-checking Trello boards. Point stakeholders to a single report that’s always up to date.

### Flexible reporting for everyone
Trello reporting doesn’t suit everyone’s needs. Export & Sync lets you keep working in Trello while enjoying the visualization and analysis tools in Google Sheets. That means your reports can look exactly how you want them — all with live data.

### True two-way sync
Your data is always updated in real-time, so each Trello board only needs to be exported once, then it’s always in sync with Unito. Change a row in Google Sheets—like due dates—and those changes will happen in Trello automatically.

### A launchpad for 30+ integrations
Export & Sync is just one of many Power-Ups and integrations from Unito. Add them to your board and sync Jira issues, Asana tasks, GitHub issues, and more.

## Supported fields
Export & Sync sends cards from your entire Trello board to Google Sheets and supports all custom fields as well as these standard fields:
- Link to card
- Title
- Description
- Board name
- Start date
- Updated at
- Due date
- Label
- List
- Status

After you export your Trello data, your Google Sheet will continue to update automatically whenever a card is added or changed in your board. You can then add rules to filter cards and additional field mappings through Unito’s standalone platform. 

---

## Helpful Links
- [Step-by Step Guide and FAQ](https://guide.unito.io/export-sync-guide?utm_source=trello&utm_medium=marketplace&utm_campaign=exportandsync)
- [Demo Video](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6ZlcT9CkpuU&ab_channel=Unito)
- [Start a Free Trial with Unito](https://unito.io/?utm_source=trello&utm_medium=marketplace&utm_campaign=exportandsync)

## Get started for free now!
Install the Power-Up and the Trello embed experience will take you through the setup process. Unito’s Export & Sync is free to try for 14 days, no credit card required. After that, you'll need to subscribe to one of our paid plans. 

## How is Export & Sync different from Unito?
Export & Sync does two things: export your Trello data to Google Sheets and keep it in sync. 

Unito’s standalone platform can pull data out of 30+ other tools and keep everything up to date across your entire tool stack. 

Here are a few other things that only Unito’s standalone platform can do:
- Create rules that filter out Trello cards.
- Build flows that create new work items in both tools.
- Sync data from tools like Asana, Jira, Airtable, Wrike, and more.

By accessing your Export & Sync exports through Unito’s standalone platform, you can add rules, try additional tools and more!

Want to try Unito’s standalone platform? Just go [here.](https://unito.io/?utm_source=trello&utm_medium=marketplace&utm_campaign=exportandsync)
